00:44.656 --> 00:48.585
Things not said, advice not given,

00:49.161 --> 00:53.664
envelopes unstamped,
regrets enveloping me.

00:58.926 --> 01:01.218
Is it easier there? I wonder.

01:02.781 --> 01:05.851
I ponder, I guess... Yes.

01:07.156 --> 01:09.046
I guess, yes.

01:18.132 --> 01:19.601
What's Mom doing back?

01:23.820 --> 01:26.578
Do you think of
me as I do of you, my son?

01:27.429 --> 01:28.500
My son.

01:29.171 --> 01:30.703
My... son.

01:30.728 --> 01:32.273
You're a cutie, aren't you?

01:32.297 --> 01:34.732
Oh, you're the cutest baby
in the world.

01:34.757 --> 01:37.935
Yes, you are.
Yes, you are.

01:37.960 --> 01:39.138
Oh, my goodness.

01:39.162 --> 01:40.696
- Randall?
- Yes.

01:40.730 --> 01:43.310
We've really got to get
our day going, Randall.

01:43.335 --> 01:44.876
Oh, of course. Sorry.

01:44.900 --> 01:47.593
No. All this talk about adoption
is giving me baby fever, right?

01:47.837 --> 01:49.871
♪ I got baby fever ♪

01:49.906 --> 01:51.573
♪ He got baby fever... ♪

01:51.742 --> 01:53.320
Okay, that's gonna have
to do it for today, buddy.

01:53.344 --> 01:55.145
Yeah, you're right. Sorry.

01:55.984 --> 01:57.195
Happy birthday, Randall.

01:57.220 --> 01:59.335
Thanks, guys.
It's gonna be a great year.

01:59.675 --> 02:02.276
The things you'll do, I'll never know.

02:02.640 --> 02:03.835
The pain.

02:04.986 --> 02:06.000
The secrets.

02:09.693 --> 02:10.991
Mom, where's Dad?

02:11.017 --> 02:12.884
- What's wrong?
- Nothing's wrong.

02:13.117 --> 02:15.270
Everything's fine. We're gonna sit down

02:15.295 --> 02:17.164
and explain everything to you guys.

02:17.189 --> 02:19.190
Oh, to be given a chance,

02:19.723 --> 02:21.968
a start, the restart,

02:22.193 --> 02:23.585
the fresh start.

02:24.261 --> 02:26.898
The crowd goes wild!

02:27.234 --> 02:30.546
You are gonna crush
this audition, babe.

02:30.571 --> 02:33.187
- You're gonna crush it.
- Oh, you think?

02:33.212 --> 02:34.976
Oh, man. All right.

02:38.164 --> 02:39.250
That is so sweet.

02:39.275 --> 02:40.441
Happy birthday to you.

02:40.496 --> 02:41.242
Oh...

02:41.267 --> 02:42.434
You ready?

02:42.510 --> 02:44.203
- Make a wish.
- Okay.

02:47.919 --> 02:48.881
Aah!

02:48.906 --> 02:50.708
- Ow, ow, ow, no, no.
- Oh, my God, I'm so sorry.

02:50.732 --> 02:53.100
Will love come for
you, as it did for me?

02:53.411 --> 02:55.507
Find you, wreck you,

02:55.546 --> 02:58.181
save you, change you?

02:58.208 --> 03:00.320
Sophie got carried away.

03:00.610 --> 03:01.914
Baby, I love you,

03:02.612 --> 03:04.976
and I wanted to bring you
to the perfect place

03:05.001 --> 03:06.640
and I wanted to say the perfect thing.

03:08.346 --> 03:09.835
But I can't say the perfect thing

03:09.860 --> 03:11.398
because you are the perfect thing.

03:12.462 --> 03:14.882
So... what do you say?

03:16.361 --> 03:17.595
Will you marry me?

03:19.594 --> 03:20.861
And cut.

03:21.117 --> 03:22.484
Very nice, very nice, Kevin.

03:22.518 --> 03:24.419
I could feel the tennis ball welling up.

03:24.453 --> 03:26.490
Really? So, when we film Emma's side,

03:26.538 --> 03:28.593
we just... plop her
down in there like that?

03:28.617 --> 03:31.179
Well, it's a little more complex
than just plopping,

03:31.204 --> 03:32.704
but, uh, yeah.

03:32.729 --> 03:34.897
Huh, I mean, technology, huh?
It's crazy.

03:35.314 --> 03:38.375
Yeah, it is, and you know what
else is kind of crazy, Kevin?

03:39.846 --> 03:42.648
♪ Happy birthday to you. ♪

03:43.432 --> 03:45.099
And if life breaks for you

03:45.134 --> 03:46.937
the way it would not break for me,

03:46.962 --> 03:49.578
if love hunts you,
finds you, captures you,

03:49.847 --> 03:51.398
will you hold it tight...

03:52.328 --> 03:54.820
nurture it, protect it?

03:55.837 --> 03:56.992
Let's go. Come on.

03:57.413 --> 03:58.703
I hope you will.

03:59.199 --> 04:00.281
I hope you can.

04:00.306 --> 04:01.835
What the hell is going on?

04:04.109 --> 04:06.343
This father's advice is not required,

04:06.378 --> 04:07.578
it has no call,

04:08.304 --> 04:10.648
so instead I'll share some
from another.

04:10.725 --> 04:12.375
- Hi, sweetheart.
- Hi, Dad.

04:13.024 --> 04:14.891
It's better to have loved and lost

04:15.387 --> 04:17.296
than to never have loved at all.

04:23.419 --> 04:25.132
Your mom and I want to talk to you.

04:29.171 --> 04:33.601
Subs & corrections by susinz.
Synced by kOoL tHuG
